title: Bug 121170 - get column label from meta data object should return some user recognizable strings
OB: The method 'get column label' does not return any user recognizable strings from the meta data object. The labels returned are null before the extraction process.
EB: The 'get column label' method should return user recognizable strings from the meta data object. The labels returned should not be null.
SR:
To reproduce the issue: 
1. Obtain a meta data object.
2. Call the 'get column label' method on the meta data object.
3. Verify that the labels returned are null.
